To achieve an objective of “Operational Efficiency” and establish a better control and governance, 
GSOC India team has developed an inhouse “Health-Check” automation application “Device Health Monitoring & Trend Analysis Dashboard”.
This application gives a single view on the health status for Cameras, Achievers, Servers and Controllers all over Western Union locations.
This application indicates the live status or triggers the actual downtime for any of the services.








Meet the new Device Health & Status Monitoring solution—real-time visibility, flexible filtering, and actionable insights to keep the organization running smoothly.”

Manual logs and static reports are slow, error-prone, and reactive.



Our system pings every device continuously, updates status in real time, archives history, and delivers trend-based maintenance recommendations.”


Open your browser, navigate to the dashboard, and securely log in. Instantly see your Global Summary: total devices, online vs. offline, and regional breakdowns.”


One-click region filters isolate APAC, EMEA, LACA, or NAMER. Toggle All, Online, or Offline devices. Refine by device type to zero in on cameras, controllers, servers—and see trends over any period.”


Drill down to the city or site level—Pune, Manila, and more—for deep down analysis and understanding of the hardware.”

 Our system help to transform the operations by enabling:
	1.	Real-Time Visibility
	2.	Dynamic Filtering
	3.	Actionable Offline Alerts
	4.	Failure Trend Identification
	5.	30-Day Historical Analysis”


Faster incident response, reduced downtime, smarter maintenance schedules, and clear accountability. With upcoming predictive analytics and advanced alerting, this dashboard scales with your needs.”


Transform device management from reactive to proactive. This system not only improves operational efficiency but also plays a crucial role in ensuring the security infrastructure remains resilient and reliable.

